--> JVM manages memory using heap for objects, stack for method execution, and garbage collection for automatic memory cleanup

###    Heap Memory 
->Purpose: Stores objects and instance variables
->All objects created using new are stored here
->Shared among all threads
->Garbage Collector works on Heap memory

###      Stack Memory 
Purpose: Method execution and local storage
Stores:
       ->Local variables
       ->Method calls
       ->Reference variables
-> Thread-specific (each thread has its own stack)
-> Memory is freed automatically when method execution ends
-> Very fast access

###   Method Area / MetaSpace
-> Purpose: Stores class-level information
-> Class metadata
-> Static variables
-> Method bytecode
-> From Java 8 onwards, Method Area is replaced by MetaSpace
-> MetaSpace is allocated outside the Heap


